LESSONS LEARNED — GOTCHAS
================================================

1. Old Helm repo (charts.karpenter.sh) is dead
   Use: oci://public.ecr.aws/karpenter/karpenter

2. OIDC provider must be registered in IAM
   Not just present in EKS — easy to miss!

3. On Windows Git Bash — never inline JSON
   Always use file:// approach

4. t3.micro = Free Tier eligible
   t3.small/medium/large = NOT Free Tier
   Use t3.micro for personal AWS accounts

5. Instance Profile policy missing from
   official docs — must add manually

6. Subnet + SG must have tag:
   karpenter.sh/discovery = cluster-name

7. Karpenter resource requests must be
   small on t3.micro nodes (256Mi not 1Gi)

